Name: Description
Data-class: An object for storing data for analysis using data-limited methods

Name: Name
Data-class: The name of the case-study

Name: Year
Data-class: A vector of years that correspond to catch and relative abundance data

Name: Cat
Data-class: Total annual catches

Name: Ind
Data-class: Relative abundance index

Name: t
Data-class: The number of years corresponding to AvC and Dt

Name: AvC
Data-class: Average catch over time t

Name: Dt
Data-class: Depletion over time t e.g. Bnow/Bthen

Name: ML
Data-class: Mean length time series

Name: Mort
Data-class: Natural mortality rate

Name: FMSY_M
Data-class: An assumed ratio of FMSY to M

Name: BMSY_B0
Data-class: The most productive stock size relative to unfished

Name: L50
Data-class: Length at 50 percent maturity

Name: L95
Data-class: Length at 95 percent maturity

Name: Lbar
Data-class: Mean length of catches over Lc (modal length)

Name: Lc
Data-class: Modal length

Name: LFC
Data-class: Length at first capture

Name: LFS
Data-class: smallest Length at full selection

Name: CAA
Data-class: Catch at Age data

Name: Dep

Data-class: Weight-Length parameter alpha

Name: wlb
Data-class: Weight-Length parameter beta

Data-class: Maximum age

Data-class: A log of events

Data-class: CV for recent recruitment strength

Data-class: Recent recruitment strength

Name: MPrec
Data-class: The previous recommendation of a management proceedure

Name: MPeff
Data-class: The current level of effort

Data-class: The last historical year of the simulation (before projection)
